WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.280
Here's a quick easy way to test the fuse with a multimeter.

2
00:00:02.280 --> 00:00:03.240
So take your multimeter.

3
00:00:03.240 --> 00:00:06.120
Let's turn it to our continuity, and we

4
00:00:06.120 --> 00:00:07.480
want to hear that beeping noise.

5
00:00:07.480 --> 00:00:11.720
If the fuse is good, we'll hear that beep.

6
00:00:11.720 --> 00:00:15.000
So on the Cobra, fuse box is right under the dash.

7
00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:16.600
You can see we have our fuses.

8
00:00:16.600 --> 00:00:18.520
And instead of pulling out every single fuse

9
00:00:18.520 --> 00:00:20.320
to see if it's disconnected, all you got to do

10
00:00:20.320 --> 00:00:24.840
is take your probes, put them into that little slot,

11
00:00:24.840 --> 00:00:25.600
and you hear the beep.

12
00:00:25.600 --> 00:00:26.480
We know it's good.

13
00:00:26.480 --> 00:00:27.880
If we don't hear a beep, then that

14
00:00:27.880 --> 00:00:29.680
means the fuse is broken, and that's

15
00:00:29.680 --> 00:00:30.680
all we need to replace.

16
00:00:30.680 --> 00:00:32.400
It saves you a lot of time from just randomly

17
00:00:32.400 --> 00:00:34.920
having to pull fuses out.

